# Git Commit Author (Cursor Agent)

When Cursor agent commits changes on behalf of the user (not as the user), use the following author so that GitHub correctly resolves the Cursor Agent avatar:

- **Author Name**: `Cursor Agent`
- **Author Email**: `199161495+cursoragent@users.noreply.github.com`

This uses GitHub's noreply format (`ID+USERNAME@users.noreply.github.com`) linking to the official [cursoragent](https://github.com/cursoragent) user, ensuring the commit shows the correct icon on GitHub.

## Usage

```bash
GIT_AUTHOR_NAME="Cursor Agent" \
GIT_AUTHOR_EMAIL="199161495+cursoragent@users.noreply.github.com" \
GIT_COMMITTER_NAME="Cursor Agent" \
GIT_COMMITTER_EMAIL="199161495+cursoragent@users.noreply.github.com" \
git commit -m "message"
```

## Do NOT use

- `cursor@users.noreply.github.com` — invalid format, avatar won't resolve
- `cursoragent@users.noreply.github.com` — may work for older accounts, but ID-prefixed form is recommended
